      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">12.503</ph> Applicability of certain
				laws to Executive agency contracts for the acquisition of commercial
				items.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d711e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d732e10" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
							           
							The following laws are not applicable
							to Executive agency contracts for the acquisition of commercial
							items:</p>
               <ol id="d711e23" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e16" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.chapter 65</xref>,
									Contracts for Materials, Supplies, Articles, and Equipment Exceeding $10,000 (see <xref href="Subpart_22.6.dita#FAR_Subpart_22_6"
                              base="i1097464"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  22.6</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e26" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.3901(b)</xref> and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C.2306(b)</xref>,
									Contingent Fees (see <xref href="3.404.dita#FAR_3_404"
                              base="i1124454"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">3.404</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e39" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.1708(e)(3)</xref>,
									Minimum Response Time for Offers (see <xref href="5.203.dita#FAR_5_203"
                              base="i1120755"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">5.203</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e49" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.chapter 81</xref>,
									Drug-Free Workplace (see <xref href="23.501.dita#FAR_23_501"
                              base="i1094542"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">23.501</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e59" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(5)</ph>
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">31 U.S.C.1354(a)</xref>,
									Limitation on use of appropriated funds for contracts with entities
									not meeting veterans’ employment reporting requirements (see <xref href="22.1302.dita#FAR_22_1302"
                              base="i1096055"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">22.1302</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e69" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(6)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
									               
									[Reserved]</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e74" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(7)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
									               
									Section
									806(a)(3) of Pub. L. 102-190, as amended by Sections 2091 and 8105
									of Pub. L. 103-355, (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C. 2302</xref> note),
									Payment Protections for Subcontractors and Suppliers (see <xref href="28.106-6.dita#FAR_28_106_6"
                              base="i1088884"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">28.106-6</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e85" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(8)</ph>
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 4706(d)(1)</xref> and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C. 2313(c)(1)</xref>,
									GAO Access to Contractor Employees, Section 871 of Pub. L. 110-417
									(see <xref href="52.214-26.dita#FAR_52_214_26"
                              base="i1060206"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.214-26</xref> and <xref href="52.215-2.dita#FAR_52_215_2"
                              base="i1059150"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.215-2</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e101" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(9)</ph>
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41U.S. C.2303,</xref> Policy
									on Personal Conflicts of Interest by Contractor Employees (see subpart <xref href="Subpart_3.11.dita#FAR_Subpart_3_11"
                              base="i1123546"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">3.11</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d732e111" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
							           
							Certain
							requirements of the following laws are not applicable to executive
							agency contracts for the acquisition of commercial items:</p>
               <ol id="d711e174" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e117" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title22-section2593a&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">22 U.S.C. 2593e</xref>, Requirement
									for a certification under Measures Against Persons Involved in Activities
									that Violate Arms Control Treaties or Agreements with the United
									States (see <xref href="9.109.dita#FAR_9_109"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">9.109</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e127" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">40 U.S.C.chapter 37</xref>,
									Requirement for a certificate and clause under the Contract Work
									Hours and Safety Standards statute (see <xref href="22.305.dita#FAR_22_305"
                              base="i1098333"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">22.305</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e137" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.8703</xref> and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">8703</xref>, Requirement
									for a clause and certain other requirements related to kickbacks
									(see <xref href="3.502.dita#FAR_3_502"
                              base="i1124348"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">3.502</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e150" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">49 U.S.C.40118</xref>, Requirement
									for a clause under the Fly American provisions (see <xref href="47.405.dita#FAR_47_405"
                              base="i1070062"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">47.405</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d732e160" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
							           
							The applicability
							of the following laws have been modified in regards to Executive
							agency contracts for the acquisition of commercial items:</p>
               <ol id="d711e234" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e166" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.4704</xref> and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C.2402</xref>, Prohibition
									on Limiting Subcontractor Direct Sales to the United States (see <xref href="3.503.dita#FAR_3_503"
                              base="i1124393"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">3.503</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e179" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.chapter 35,</xref> Truthful
									Cost or Pricing Data, and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C.2306a</xref>, Truth
									in Negotiations Act (see <xref href="15.403.dita#FAR_15_403"
                              base="i1105934"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">15.403</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d732e192" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.chapter 15</xref>,
									Cost Accounting Standards (48 CFR Chapter 99) (see <xref href="12.214.dita#FAR_12_214"
                              base="i1113603"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">12.214</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
